I have found all or nearly all of them in Ben Jonson, Beaumont and Fletcher, Marlowe, and other poets and drama- tists of the time3 indeed, they are so commonly used that without them it is hardly possible to conceive how anybody could write or speak the English lan- guage. M. Bucke, who asserts that they were originated by Bacon, who uses them constantly both in his acknow- ledged work and in the work of Shakespeare.
